      <trans-unit id="tpl.foot"><source>* Unique visitors over multi-day ranges are approximated as the sum of daily values (not exact when added up). Daily values are exact. Data is read-only from the cube database.</source></trans-unit>

      <!-- Onboarding (cube DB empty) / no access -->
      <trans-unit id="tpl.noAccess.title"><source>No access to any analytics site</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.noAccess.text"><source>Site mappings are configured, but your backend account has no web mount on any mapped site. Ask an administrator to grant access to the page tree of the site you need.</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.title"><source>No data yet – set up the ingestion pipeline</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.intro"><source>This module only reads pre-aggregated data. It needs the SightMetrics ingestion pipeline (a separate DuckDB-based container/cron job outside TYPO3) to fill the cube database – three steps:</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.step1.title"><source>Create the cube database</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.step1.text"><source>A MariaDB/MySQL database (e.g. "analytics") with a write user for the ingestion (cube_rw) and a SELECT-only user for this module (report_ro).</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.step2.title"><source>Run the ingestion nightly</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.step2.text"><source>Deploy the ingestion container (or cron job) with your sites.conf and the CUBE_DSN secret; it parses the web server logs and writes daily aggregates. Kubernetes manifests and a runbook are included in the repository.</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.step3.title"><source>Connect TYPO3</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.step3.text"><source>Configure the read-only "cube" database connection in additional.php and map your TYPO3 sites via sightmetrics_site_id. Then verify the setup:</source></trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="tpl.ob.docs"><source>Documentation and ingestion pipeline on GitHub →</source></trans-unit>

